deck_excerpt: Synchronized Realm FTK ft. Junk Speeder
deck_description:
So, Junk Speeder decks are known with their Synchro Summon mechanics. Why not make it deadly with Synchronized Realm?

 

 

Gameplan

1) Assuming Coral/Cardian is present onboard and you have a Level 1 monster in your hand, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop...

  • Around 0:35-0:40 timestamp, Junk Speeder + Nitro Synchron = Nitro Warrior was the play to draw a card with Nitro Synchron. Since Signal Warrior was placed by accident, I had to banish Signal as LIGHT to recover it to Extra Deck with "Primal Seed".
  • Though not seen in this video, there is a chance you might have drawn 2 x Realm cards so late and used all Level 1 monsters to the GY, including Jester. In that case, banish Jester as DARK.
  • Always reserve one copy of "De-Synchro" in your hand, for that you need to repeat it with "Primal Seed" loop to bring forth Signal while burning with Realm.

2) Coral/Cardian + Level 1 = Signal is your equation. Repeat with "De-Synchro" when 2 x Realm cards are active to burn your opponent. Know that you can also burn with Signal by using counters "Synchro World" has.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Reinforcement of the Army" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Flower Cardian Moonflowerviewing" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Junk Converter" + "Junk Speeder" can be found within "Scrap Iron Soldiers" Secret Pack to save 90 SR and 30 UR!

- "Jet Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found either within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" or "Stardust Ties" Secret Packs to save 60 SR!

- These following cards can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 210 SR and 60 UR:

  • 3 x Junk Synchron >>> 90 SR
  • 2 x Synchronized Realm >>> 60 SR
  • 1 x Signal Warrior >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Ravenous >>> 30 SR
  • 2 x Primal Seed >>> 60 UR

- These following cards can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 180 SR and 60 UR:

  • 1 x Stardust Wurm >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Stardust Synchron >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Wheel Synchron >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Stardust Illumination >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Duelist Genesis >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x On Your Mark, Get Set, DUEL! >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon >>> 30 UR
  • 1 x Crimson Dragon >>> 30 UR

 

So, in total, you can save up to 690 SR and 210 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Everything in Masterduel changed when the Tenpai Nation attacked...
deck_description:
Everything in Masterduel changed when the Tenpai Nation attacked... Everything is blinding second, and duelists insta-leave when they get their board broken! One turn kill your opponent with the force of a million nuclear bombs with the absurdly high attack power of Tenpai - up to 35400 total lifepoint damage! Not only are these dragons unaffected by activated effects during Main Phase 1 through their archetypal field spell, these cards are so consistent that you can jam 24+ staples in the deck! and You can inundate your opponent with a flurry of handtraps and boardbreakers then proceed to your opponent's final reckoning as you enter the Battle Phase.

I admit, I'm not the most "skillful" duelist. I generally don't think 3 turns ahead, play 4 dimensional chess, predict what's in my opponent's hand, etc. That's why I LOVE decks like Tenpai - it makes dueling so easy and simple that even a "Yugi-Boomer" like me can win against meta! I've always been a player who loves "aggro" playstyles and I find it sooo unbelievably satisfying dismantling boards and control decks. Naturally, a blind second meta deck is the perfect deck for me (and perhaps for you as well) on Masterduel ladder!

Get that Masters 1 in record time with extremely quick and cheesy games with the explosive, devastating and ridiculously powerful Tenpai Dragon!

If you want a detailed guide and combo on how to use the deck, check out my earlier article by clicking here. 


GLHF Duelists!

deck_excerpt: She Morph on my Metal til I Unchain
deck_description:
Just a lil somehting I cooked up in anticipation of the new Metalmorph cards. When I was first grtting back into Yugioh these were the first cards I saw were announced and I've been excited foe them to drop.

Unfortunately Metalmorph plays a smaller role in the deck in total but it's made to supplement and bridge the gap between Dragon Link and Unchained.

A typical play wants to push out as much Dragon Link as you can and to set up Metalmorph for the next turn, then jump into Unchained because you'll be locked out of non-fiends once you start comboing.

Final Beinger of the end times was a surprise pull from ROTA that works phenomonally well in Unchained, allowing me to pop my own monster and any card on my opponents field for a double plus; as well as that, it's superior to Escape of the Unchained because it won't fizzle if my opponent removes their targeted spell before it resolves. The difference between them bith being Escape needs to pop both targets while End Times will resolve regardless.

deck_excerpt: Hiro Mill OTK ft. Junk Speeder
deck_description:
Good day to you! A long time ago, I have depleted my opponent's deck thanks to Panda alongside Hiro. So, I decided to do it again with Junk Speeder.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Draw your whole deck. If you go second and your opponent has their side filled up, clean 3 x Main Monster Zone (MMZ) with Ravenous/Coral/Baronne/Legatia. If you go first and your opponent has 3 x MMZ empty, have Dragster and Baronne at your side for protection.

2) If you have played "Into the Void" beforehand, set all four Traps and end your turn, resulting into Wattfox and Wanghu being sent to GY. However, you can also send Wattfox to GY with Junk Converter seen right at the beginning of the video, which is okay.

3) When it's your opponent's Draw Phase, activate these Traps as illustrated below:

  1. Powerful Rebirth >>> Wattfox
  2. Give and Take >>> Wanghu
  3. Reverse Reuse >>> MJ #2 as face-down and Hiro as face-up
  4. All-Out Attacks

3) What is going to happen is that Wanghu destroys Wattfox, which shuts down anything your opponent can try to break you, including hand-traps. Then, via All-Out Attacks, MJ #2 will flip face-up and you can start milling your opponent. While your Traps are resolving, you can protect yourself with Dragster and Baronne, in case your opponent activates something to disrupt your combo...

  • I would like to also mention that, around 7:50 timestamp of the video, you should change Card Position to Auto and Activation Order Settings to Off. Thus, you will save a lot of time and make things automated.

4) After your job is done with Traps, MJ #2 is going to excavate three monsters, which are MJ #2 + Hiro + Wanghu. Then, your opponent draws 3 cards each time Hiro has been activated. So, sit back and place MJ #2 + Hiro + Wanghu while watching your opponent milling themselves uncontrollably to win the game eventually.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Reinforcement of the Army" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Flower Cardian Moonflowerviewing" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "F.A. Dawn Dragster" can be found within "Tournament Athletes" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Baronne de Fleur" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Junk Converter" + "Junk Speeder" can be found within "Scrap Iron Soldiers" Secret Pack to save 90 SR and 30 UR!

- "Jet Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found either within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" or "Stardust Ties" Secret Packs to save 30 SR!

- These following cards can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 180 SR:

  • 3 x Junk Synchron >>> 90 SR
  • 1 x King Tiger Wanghu >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x All-Out Attacks >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Ravenous >>> 30 SR

- These following cards can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 180 SR and 60 UR:

  • 1 x Stardust Wurm >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Stardust Synchron >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Wheel Synchron >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Stardust Illumination >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Duelist Genesis >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x On Your Mark, Get Set, DUEL! >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon >>> 30 UR
  • 1 x Crimson Dragon >>> 30 UR

 

So, in total, you can save up to 630 SR and 210 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Ohm FTK ft. Telefon + Junk Speeder
deck_description:
Hello there! In this deck, the opponent will be burned to death by Ohm and Telefon duo. Let's get into action!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Synchro Summon Maple with Coral/Cardian and Level 1 Non-Tuner as materials. Then, choose DARK as Attribute. Make sure you have 3 x Main Monster Zones (MMZ) reserved for 1 x Ohm + 2 x Telefon...

  • If you want to try out other cards seen in Side Deck, don't forget to pick up correct Attribute with Maple.

2) Place Opal and Flash on Pendulum Zones and Pendulum Summon 1 x Ohm + 2 x Telefon. Since all monsters you have are DARK and 2 x Telefon can cycle themselves to revive, you can burn down your opponent for certain. Starting from 6:45 timestamp of the video, you can see it for yourself.

So, in total, you can save up to 630 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

deck_excerpt: Centur-Ion's hyper consistent nature with the power of Bystials to counter the metagame make for a powerful ladder deck!
deck_description:
Have you wanted a hyper consistent ladder deck that can still field a ton of handtraps, hardcounter the meta with bystials, play through Maxx "C," Droll, and Shifter? Well Centur-Ion Bystial is the deck for you!

With the added power of the Bystials, Centur-Ion can counter a metagame full of light/dark monsters to banish in the GY like I:P Masquerena, Fallen of Albaz, Unchained Soul of Yama, and Yubel! Bystials also grant Centur-Ion level 6 bodies to access the coveted level 10 synchro boss monster line-up like Dis Pater, Chengying and Chaos Angel!
 
The hyper consistent nature of Centur-Ions means that this deck can play a whopping 14 handtraps, meaning you'll almost always handtrap your opponent to a standstill or a weakened gamestate and outgrind your opponent with sheer mechanical might and the power of friendship!

I personally think mechas and mecha pilots are the coolest thing ever, especially in Yugioh, so this is my new favourite deck for the time being. YOUR DRILL WILL PIERCE THE HEAVENS WITH CENTUR-ION!
 
GLHF DUELISTS!

If you want a detailed guide on how to play this deck, click here!
 
Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_excerpt: If I can't otk, I'll just make 5 disruptions lol
deck_description:
The idea behind this deck is that opening sangen summoning, sangen kaimen, dora dora or tenpai dragon paidra can set up 2 level 3 monsters, which is enough for full goblin combo, while still being able to do the tenpai OTK. You can also, if stopped trying to do tenpai, very easily just go directly into goblin biker combo, either with what is already in play, or with one of the many extenders. I decided to play 50 cards so that I could play more non-engine, as I have a high density of starters but also a few cards that I don't want to draw because I can search them (though the only card you can actually open that shuts off plays is the full-armored xyz trap, because it becomes hard to get all the material off of fortress)

I explicitly request this to not be put on ygodeckprofile, the website is full of scammy ads and steals decks without crediting the person who made them, while slapping on their shitty watermark that blocks the cards.

deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Emmad Fajem

Tournament: YCS Niagara Falls – October 12th 2024

Placement: Top 32

IF YOU WANT TO KNOW HOW TO USE THE DECK READ THIS

Hand traps are obvious, just be annoying. You could add Skull Meister as another hand trap, maybe by taking out Forbidden Droplet. Pot of Avarice is for returning numerons to extra deck plus a link monster or a hand trap to draw 2. If you take out/side Pot of Avarice then also take out 1 Numeron Calling. Crossout Designator and Called by the Grave is for negating hand traps, Limiter Removal to use NOT on Infinitrack Fortress Megaclops but on the numeron gates to double attack. It's also not once per turn, so that helps. Memories of Hope makes it look like drawing cards is your job when you use it when the numeron gates are up. If your using Titanocider you probably don't need 3 as you can keep looping it. Keep in mind if you set it using its GY effect you CAN'T activate it the same turn. I put "Meta Deck" even though it can lose to some better things, but it still has pretty high potential for an FTK. If you take your opponent by surprise and/or they don't have adequate things to stop you you could win pretty damn quick. My personal favorite deck, I have used this every since I figured out the even an upgraded crystal beast structure deck and pure unchained can't really compete with other decks. Quite fun to use as well.

deck_excerpt: Azamina, Fiendsmirh, Snake-eye, white forest, Supreme Darkness
deck_description:
black witch -> Oss -> SE ash -> poplar -> field spell -> gets oak with Fspell -> SE ash + poplar = Flamberge -> poplar set itself/ash -> flamberge set opponent -> SE Damn dragon contact fusion-> S/T opponent monster.

Classic Azamina:
Deception -> Azamina  Hollow -> Mu Rcielago -> sinful spoil of choice -> send mu Rcielago to GY (sequence/little knight/close moon) -> Azamina Hollow loop -> Aza Silva.

Azamina w/ WF going first:
Deception -> Azamina  Hollow -> Mu Rcielago -> Search Azamina Elzette WF ->  send mu Rcielago to GY (sequence/little knight/close moon) -> Azamina Hollow loop -> Aza Silva ->  Special Aza Elzette -> Do some WF combo w/ Aza Elzette -> Aza Elzette Search Azamina Determination -> end on a synchro or 2. Determination during opponent turn using Sinful spoil in GY into St. Azamina -> into Regina. Regina pops if you use silva effect or if you use azamina unleashing

Aza Regina and Aza Sol Ery. needs fiend for to fusion, which Aza elzette can do using fiend on field (links) or engraver in hand (your brick draw) to fuse into either. This ends on silva, regina + Mu rciela which can reduce their attack. or just silva + sol ery.

monsters in S/T can be used for WF for cost too.

Azamina unleashing triggering in the GY can be chained with a.regina to pop 2.

1 engraver & 1x SS Deception can be cut out for handtraps/Board breaker if needed.
Pretty decent predaplant deck, side deck is just some extra stuff.
My version of the the barefoot girls
This is the deck I used to place 1st place at a Traditional Format tournament in September of 2009.

Do you love 5DS anime? Want to see what happened in Episode 140 called "Soul Binding Gate! The Sealed Future!" with your eyes? Well, what are you waiting for? It's time to rev it up!

 

 

Gameplan

1) When you have Ravenous on the field, set "Z-ONE" and discard Hedgehog + Gate with Ravenous to pop "Z-ONE". Next, "Z-ONE" triggers for you to fetch Gate from your GY to your hand.

2) Use Wok on Ravenous to gain LP to make sure you stay alive. Then, activate "Dark Hole" to clear all monsters, especially yours. It matters a lot if you want to play "Soul Binding Gate", which is now possible with all conditions being met.

3) Play Temple >>> Iron Wall combination, which lets you revive Hedgehog forever but we need a Tuner on the battlefield. This is where Fleuret comes in and you can pick up any Level 2 or lower Tuner you like. I used Formula because we are reliving the moments of 5DS anime right now.

4) Due to the wording of "Soul Binding Gate", Formula will be destroyed but we can protect it with Dress. After that, with your LP higher than your opponent, you can bring forth Hedgehog forever to deal 800 damage constantly until your opponent is dead.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon" + "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 90 SR and 30 UR!

- "Fleuret de Fleur" + "Soul Binding Gate" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "Temple of the Kings" can be either found within "The One Who Serve Ra" or "Guardian of Kings" Secret Packs to save 30 SR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 660 SR and 90 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Soul Binding Gate FTK ft. Junk Speeder
deck_description:
So, right after I made Panda version, I discovered how to do with Junk Speeder. More faithful to 5DS lore, I would say.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Unless you have drawn "Synchro World" and "Synchro Rumble", Synchro Summon "Crimson Dragon" with "Ravenous + Junk Synchron" equation and find "Synchro World" with "Crimson Dragon".

2) Activate "Synchro World" and whenever you have 2 x Main Monster Zones (MMZ) free, use "De-Synchro" to replace the equation with Legatia = Ravenous + Junk Synchron.

3) If you have drawn everything and changed the button at the bottom right corner of the screen to "ON", set Iron Wall + Z-ONE. Then, get rid of Librarian with "Stardust Synchron" and Synchro Summon "Black Rose Dragon" with whatever you have. After the activation of Rose, chain into Wok and target Legatia. Choose its ATK to have more LP than your opponent.

4) With conditions being met, you can activate "Soul Binding Gate" and "Boogie Trap". If you haven't discarded Hedgehog with "On Your Mark, Get Set, DUEL!", you can gladly do so alongside discarding "Junk Converter" with "Boogie Trap". Then, set and activate Iron Wall, which is essential to revive Hedgehog forever.

5) We need to have a Tuner for Hedgehog. So, play "Synchro Rumble" and pick up "Junk Synchron". With Soul being activated as mandatory, you have to chain into playing "Forbidden Dress" and target on "Junk Synchron" to protect itself from being detonated by Soul.

6) Finally, bring forth Hedgehog over and over until your opponent is dead.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Reinforcement of the Army" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

- "Flower Cardian Moonflowerviewing" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Soul Binding Gate" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Black Rose Dragon" can be found within "Exquisite Jet-Black Rose" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Boogie Trap" can be found within "Mother Nature's Snare" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Junk Converter" + "Junk Speeder" can be found within "Scrap Iron Soldiers" Secret Pack to save 90 SR and 30 UR!

- "Jet Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found either within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" or "Stardust Ties" Secret Packs to save 60 SR!

- "Junk Synchron" + "Ravenous" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 120 SR!

- These following cards can be found within "Evoked Dragon of Miracles" Secret Pack to save 180 SR and 60 UR:

  • 1 x Stardust Wurm >>> 30 SR
  • 1 x Stardust Synchron >>> 30 SR

So, in total, you can save up to 660 SR and 180 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

deck_excerpt: Ranked 175 (5-3) at YCS NIagara Falls - Andy Thibeault's Deck list.
deck_description:
This deck is a 50 cards variant that includes some tech possible with using the new support from Rage of The Abyss.

-Heart of the Blue-Eyes is a great searcher and also a great card interaction with your opponents summons.

-The uses of Snake-Eyes card was to help the deck have more fuel and grind power, Flamberge Dragon gets himself summoned  with the field spell during my opponent turn, since this event was composed of multiple snake-eyes variant deck, the quick effect of Flamberge got very useful against those matchups it was like fighting fire with fire i guess. (flamberge is also a Melody target) 

-Archnemesses Eschatos was my main deck Board Breaker, and it sure was efficient against Fiend(s) decks and also very efficient against mono types decks.(Also a Melody Target)

-Ghost Ogre maindeck was a way to play agains Tenpai, Yubel's Continuous Spells and such, never have i ever regreted it in the deck during the event,

- Psychic End Punisher was my way out of Dimensional Barrier and it worked, Sengengin or Flamberge or Blue-eyes + Any Level 3 Sister Tuner. Won me 3 games. 

-This deck was build with the YCS Niagara Falls 2024 Meta in mind. Went 5-3 at the event and placed 175th in 8 rounds of Swiss of 852 players)

deck_excerpt: FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE...
deck_description:
Rage of the Abyss has been released, and with it, Snake-Eyes is back on the competitive scene (like it or not)! The September 2024 banlist has all but obliterated the consistency of Snake-Eyes, leaving it with 1 Ash and 1 Poplar, but with ROTA, that problem has been largely fixed! 
 
"Deception of the Sinful Spoils" is functionally 3 more copies of any Sinful Spoils card you want, since one of the monster it summons (Mu Rcielago) searches for any Sinful Spoils with it's on-summon effect. Not only that, Deception also summons an omni-negate, Ilia Silvia - effectively rendering Snake-Eyes from interruptions like Nibiru and Bystials! 
 
Not only has Snake-Eyes been "fixed" by it's Rage of the Abyss power-ups, it has been incredibly stronger! This is bad news for anyone who thought that Snake-Eyes has been phased out of the game by the recent banlist - this deck is currently here to stay in top competitive gameplay! 

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video! 
 
ARCHETYPES, ENGINES AND DECKBUILDING
 
Diabellstar's crew post-ROTA is composed of 5 archetypes: SNAKE-EYE (deck core), the supporting sub-archetypes SINFUL-SPOILS and the new AZAMINA cards. A sizeable KASHTIRA package is also used so the duelist can play through Mulcharmy Fuwalos and for extra extension. Finally minimalistic FIENDSMITH package composed of only 1 Engraver is used. Despite the 5 archetypes present in the deck, STAPLES still form a large part of the deck due to its many 1-card starters and hyper consistent nature.
 
The SNAKE-EYE/SINFUL-SPOILS cards form the core of the deck. Although these cards have been thoroughly gouged by the September banlist, it is certainly still competitively viable with the new ROTA support. Due to the banlist, the Snake-Eye cards are greatly reduced in this deck - it is composed of x1 Ash, x1 Poplar, x2 Oak, x1 Flamberge Dragon, x1 Snake-Eye Diabellstar, x1 Temple and x1 Original Sin.  This deck core is maximized around searching or summoning from deck Snake-Eyes Ash, the heart and soul of the strategy. Snake-Eyes Ash starts up the entire gameplan, so 10 cards search it (x3 Diabellstarr, x3 WANTED, x3 Deception, x1 Original Sinful-Spoils, x3 Bonfire) in addition x1 Ash granting a total of 14 starters in a 43 card deck! With that many starters, this deck is still very consistent. 
 
AZAMINA is the new archetype debuting in Rage of the Abyss, and although it is an independent archetype, it greatly supports the consistency and power of Snake-Eyes. It is a small supplementary engine in the strategy. It is composed of x3 Deception and x1 Hallowed Azamina. It has two monsters in the Extra Deck - Ilia Silvia is the omni-negate and Mu Rcielago is the searcher. 
 
The most minimal FIENDSMITH package is used in the deck - x1 Engraver. 1 Engraver is responsible for turboing out D/D/D Wave High King Caesar, an extremely oppressive boss monster that negates summons up to twice and is a natural counter to Nibiru. 
 
The last archetype featured in this deck is a sizeable KASHTIRA package. It is composed of x2 Wraithsoth, x2 Unicorn, x1 Fenrir, and x1 Birth. Kashtira is played because it gives more cards on-field for Snake-Eyes/Sinful Spoils to use as cost for their effects. It also allows the duelist to somewhat establish a board when under the new Mulcharmy Fuwalos, since the engine doesn't summon from the Extra Deck or Deck. 
 
The STAPLES featured in this deck are 12 of the best handtraps this format - x3 Fuwalos, x3 Ash Blossom, x3 Effect Veiler and x3 Impermanence. If Fuwalos is in your hand and you're going first, simply use it as cost for Diabellstar or Deception since you cannot use it anyways when you have stuff on your field. Since handtraps are so dominant, x1 Called By is also included. 
 
The SIDING PATTERN for this deck is talking out x1 Snake-Eyes Oak, x3 Fuwalos (when you know you're going 1st), and parts or all of the Kashtira Engine. This allows the pilot to put in 10 boardbreakers to play through your opponent's gamestate to allow the engine with it's immense amount of gas to combo through and out-resource the opponent. 
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
Snake-Eye Azamina is a powerful combo deck that can link spam like no tomorrow. What is different about this deck post-ROTA is that it has extra consistency and protection with the new Azamina support archetype. 
 
A singular uninterrupted Deception of the Sinful Spoils, 1 monster and 1 card gets you 6 interruptions and provides you with incredible amounts of resources as follow-up for next turn. Here is the combo: 
 
Deception of the Sinful Spoils + 1 monster + 1 card = Ilia Silvera (Omni-negate), D/D/D Wave High King Caesar (x2 special summon negate), S:P Little Knight (Made with I:P Masquerena, x2 target banish), Promethean Princess (x1 destroy monster), Follow-up (Deception on field, Poplar/Ash search during opponent's turn, Engraver in GY, Princess in GY, Draw 1 (WANTED recycling OSS)
  1. Activate Deception of the Sinful Spoils. Activate Deception tributing the monster in your hand to add from deck Hallowed Azamina. 
  2. Activate Hallowed Azamina revealing Mu Rcielago from Extra Deck and sending Deception to the GY to summon Mu Rcielago.
  3. Mu Rcielago searches from deck Sinful Spoils WANTED from deck.
  4. Activate WANTED to search for Diabellstar from deck. 
  5. Use Diabellstar's summon effect to summon herself by sending any card from hand. 
  6. Activate Diabellstar's on-summon effect to set from deck Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye 
  7. Link summon Moon of the Closed Sky using Diabellstar + Mu Rcielago. 
  8. Activate Hallowed Azamina's effect to add itself back to the hand by returning Mu Rcielago from GY to the Extra Deck. 
  9. Activate Hallowed Azamina's effect revealing Ilia Silvera from Extra Deck and sending Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye to the GY to summon Ilia Silvera. 
  10. Link summon Fiendsmith Requiem using Moon of the Closed Sky. (The following is Fiendsmith combo to turbo out High King Caesar). 
  11. Tribute Requiem to summon from deck Engraver. 
  12. Activate Requiem's effect in GY to equip itself to Engraver. 
  13. Special summon Necroquip Princess using Requiem + Engraver.
  14. Activate Engraver's GY effect returning Requiem to the Extra Deck to summon himself. 
  15. XYZ summon D/D/D Wave High King Caesar using  Necroquip + Engraver. 
  16. Banish from the GY Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye placing Diabellstar on the bottom of the deck to search from deck Snake-Eye Ash. 
  17. Normal summon Ash. Search from deck Poplar. (The following is full Snake-Eyes combo). 
  18. Activate Poplar's effect to summon itself from hand. 
  19. Activate Poplar's on-summon effect to search from deck Divine Temple. 
  20. Link away Poplar to summon Relinquished Anima. 
  21. Activate Poplar's GY effect placing it in the backrow. 
  22. Activate Ash effect sending itself and Relinquished Anima to summon from deck Oak. 
  23. Activate Oak's on-summon effect to target Ash and summon it from the GY. 
  24. Activate Divine Temple, placing Poplar in the backrow. 
  25. Activate Oak's effect sending itself and Poplar to summon from deck Flamberge Dragon. 
  26. Link summon I:P Masquerena using Flamberge Dragon + Ash. 
  27. Activate Flamberge Dragon's GY effect to summon Ash and Oak from the GY. 
  28. Link summon Promethean Princess using I:P Masquerena + Ash. 
  29. Activate Promethean Princess' effect to summon from GY Flamberge Dragon. 
  30. Activate Flamberge Dragon's effect to place I:P Masquerena in the backrow. 
  31. Link summon Raging Phoenix using I:P Oak + Promethean Princess. 
  32. Link summon Worldsea Dragon Zealantis using Raging Phoenix. 
  33. Banish from GY WANTED targeting Original Sinful Spoils in the Banishment placing it on the bottom of the deck to draw 1 card.
  34. During the End Phase, Deception sets itself from the GY due to it being sent there this turn. 
  35. During your opponent's turn, summon I:P Masquerena from the backrow during Draw Phase using Flamberge Dragon. Then you can link summon S:P Little Knight using Flamberge Dragon + I:P Masquerena for two banishes! You can also activate Promethean Princess during an opportune time to destroy any of your fire monsters and your opponent's monster. 
HELP I GOT FUWALOS'D! WHAT DO I DO? Well duelist, here is the emergency back-up plan if you got Fuwalos'd in Snake-Eye Azamina: 

Snake-Eye Ash = S:P Little Knight (Made with I:P Masquerena, x2 target banish) + Follow-up (Poplar/Ash search during opponent's turn), Your opponent only draws 1 card from Fuwalos!
  1. Normal summon Snake-Eye Ash. Search from deck Poplar. 
  2. Activate Poplar's effect to summon itself from hand
  3. Activate Poplar's on-summon effect to search from deck Divine Temple. 
  4. Link summon I:P Masquerena. (Your opponent only draws 1 card!) (DO NOT activate Poplar's GY effect to place in the backrow). 
  5. Activate Divine Temple. Place in the backrow Flamberge Dragon. 
  6. During your opponent's turn, summon from the backrow Flamberge Dragon with Temple's effect as soon as your opponent summons a monster. Activate I:P Masquerena's effect to  link summon S:P Little Knight using Flamberge Dragon + I:P Masquerena for two banishes! At this point, we hope that your handtraps in-hand and the double banish from S:P Little Knight is enough for you to survive until next turn, because your resource generation with Flamberge Dragon + Poplar/Oak/Ash's resource loop is sufficient. 
GOING FIRST, a singular Deception of the Sinful Spoils grants you an omni-negate with Ilia Silvia, double special summon negate with Wave High King Caesar, a targeted monster destruction with Promethean Princess, and lots of bodies + follow-up + set-up GY for next turn's OTK. If you also have the Kashtira extenders, you can also end on Unicorn's Extra Deck banish, Fenrir's targeted banish, and Birth's GY banish! Next turn, you can OTK easily with tons of link material to finish the game with the likes of Accesscode Talker. Remember this is from 1 and 2 discards, so your hand may also contain one of the 12 handtraps! 
 
GOING SECOND, the Snake-Eyes Azamina strategy features a ton of handtraps and gas to weaken your opponent's gamestate or potentially end their turn on a suboptimal board so you can start comboing yourself. As you combo up, you can methodically remove your opponent's field using Flamberge Dragon's non-destruction removal, Knightmare Phoenix's S/T destruction, Engraver's targeted send, Accesscode can be made for up to 3 pops due to the different attribute link material in the GY (dark-Anima, fire- Knightmare Phoenix, light-Requiem). 
 
GENERAL TIPS
  • Always try to insulate your plays with Ilia Silvia. Either your opponent will be forced to spend an interruption stopping Deception of Hallowed Azamina, or you get to continue full combo! 
  • Good bait for your opponent's interruptions (like Ash and Imperm) is the Kashtira engine or the Azamina engine. After you bait their handtrap, you can move on to comboing. 
  • If you have Snake-Eyes Ash and you drew into Original Sinful Spoils already, when you search with Poplar take Snake-Eyes Divine Temple instead so that it's an additional extender. The extra card in the backrow serves as an extender for your Snake-Eyes cost to send a card on the field to the GY. 
  • Snake-Eyes summons so many times (even on the opponent's turn!) that you'd sometimes find yourself in the awkward position of having no more space on your board! Be careful of this scenario. A good way to get around this situation during your opponent's turn is to link away as much monsters as possible with I:P Masquerena. 
  • Other builds of this deck include summoning Silhouhatte Rabbit for more interruptions or summoning Fiendsmith's Desirae. The Extra Deck is super tight so I opted to not use cards in my build. Feel free to customize the Extra Deck in your own build of this deck to for your own playstyle! 
  • The siding pattern for this deck is talking out x1 Snake-Eyes Oak, x3 Fuwalos (when you know you're going 1st), and parts or all of the Kashtira Engine. This allows the duelist to side in 10+ cards!
  • Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
CONCLUDING COMMENTARY
 
FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. FOUR MORE MONTHS OF SNAKE-EYE. Greetings! This FTK setup is similar to one I did as Panda back then.

 

 

Gameplan

1) When you have drawn everything, replace Librarian with "Stardust Synchron" and set Rebirth. Then, Synchro Summon "Black Rose Dragon" with whatever you have to destroy everything on the field, including Rebirth.

2) Activate Boogie to discard Junk Converter + Yajiro Invader to set Rebirth. Then, you can activate Rebirth and pick Dragon to change Types of monsters in either GYs.

3) Revive Yajiro with "Monster Reborn" but you have to place Yajiro on the center of the battlefield or Yajiro will explode. Then, give it to your opponent with "Shien's Spy".

4) Activate "Vision with Eyes of Blue" away from Yajiro and reveal Blue-Eyes to Special Summon Blue-Eyes at where Yajiro would pop it. This results Deep-Eyes to trigger itself, which lets you Special Summon it and deal tons of damage. Though this deck doesn't have lots of Dragons by default, Rebirth can change the results to boost Deep-Eyes...

  • Though not seen in this gameplay, you can deal more damage with Deep-Eyes another time. All you have to do is place Deep-Eyes opposite to Yajiro back in #4. Then, use Vision to return Deep-Eyes to hand and Special Summon Blue-Eyes from your hand at where Yajiro would pop it. Repeat what you did back then with Deep-Eyes to seal the game for certain.

A list currated for use in Domain Format: Join the Discord!

This list of 60 cards mainly relate to advantages that show up against multiple opponents or in Domain Format’s unique deckbuilding restrictions.
As such, I tried my best to exclude cards that good regardless of format in Yugioh. 

Domain Format General Rules:

  • Singleton Format: Every card restricted to 1 copy per deck.
  • 60-card Format: Every main deck must contain exactly 60 cards.
  • 4-player Pods: Each player fights for themseleves in an all-out brawl. You will have 3 opponents.
  • Deckmaster Restrictions: Each player chooses a "Deckmaster" to restrict the types and attributes their deck can contain (matches the Deckmaster). Deckmasters may be summoned from a specfied "Deckmaster Zone" with normal summoning rules. 
  • Refer here for additional exceptions or exclusions.

Similar Cards

Cards like Dark Hole or Malevolent Catastrophe :
Boardwipes: Refer to this deck link.

Notable Spell or Trap boardwipes are Full House , Hey, Trunade! and Fairy Wind

Reuseable Spell or Trap Destruction: Unending Nightmare

Allows a resummon of your Deckmaster: Ultimeat Offering , Supermagic Sword of Raptinus , Free-Range Monsters , Arrivalrivals , Summon Dice

Removes cards at every opponent's End Phase: Ectoplasmer 

Please leave suggestions, critiques, or questions below.

deck_excerpt: Orca, Mega-Fortress of Darkness makes a splash
deck_description: Based on Orca Mega-Fortress of Darkness, Orca Water Aggro uses A Legendary Ocean to dodge the tribute requirement of Orca's summon. ​Cannonball Spear Shellfish and Torpedo Fish are then fired off as targeted removal, clearing the path for the killer whale to attack. Mermaid Knight makes quick work of goat tokens, allowing Orca's guns to hit more important targets. Abyssal Warrior benefits from A Legendary Ocean while providing additional board control and Mother Grizzly allows for card selection The deck also benefits from Salvage and Terraforming to help with maintaining card advantage and consistency.

Overall Strategy

Your deck focuses on stalling your opponent and setting up the win condition with Destiny Board and its Spirit Message cards. While you are waiting for Destiny Board to win the game over five turns, you’ll rely on defensive monsters, backrow protection, and field control to survive. You'll gradually reduce the opponent's resources, while maintaining your own board, so you can establish Destiny Board without interruption.

Key Phases of the Game

Early Game (Turns 1-3)

  • Primary Goal: Establish your defense and start thinning your deck to draw into Destiny Board and protective cards.

  1. Activate Stall Engines:

    • Set Gravekeeper’s Spy or Gravekeeper’s Guard to establish your defense early.
    • Use Battle Fader to stop any direct attacks and stall for a turn.
    • Activate Messenger of Peace to prevent attacks from larger monsters.

  2. Search for Key Cards:

    • Use Gold Sarcophagus to fetch Destiny Board or any important card needed for defense (Mirror Force, Solemn Judgment, etc.).
    • Gravekeeper’s Commandant can search for Necrovalley to block effects that rely on the graveyard.

  3. Defensive Backrow:

    • Set cards like Waboku, Threatening Roar, or Dark Bribe early to protect against attacks or backrow removal from the opponent.
    • If you have Starlight Road in hand, set it to counter cards like Heavy Storm or Torrential Tribute while summoning Stardust Dragon.

Mid Game (Turns 4-6)

  • Primary Goal: Stabilize your defense and get Destiny Board on the field.

  1. Start the Destiny Board Win Condition:

    • Once you have enough protection set up, activate Destiny Board and start placing the Spirit Messages.
    • Ensure you have at least 2-3 defensive options (such as Dark Bribe, Threatening Roar, Necrovalley) before flipping Destiny Board to protect it from cards like Mystical Space Typhoon.

  2. Strengthen Your Stall:

    • Keep using Gravekeeper's Spy to bring out another copy and wall off the opponent.
    • Use Gravekeeper’s Guard to return high-threat monsters to your opponent’s hand, forcing them to spend resources re-summoning.

  3. Control the Board:

    • Use Kycoo the Ghost Destroyer or Necrovalley to control graveyard-heavy decks like Lightsworn and stop cards like Judgment Dragon from being summoned.
    • Utilize Book of Moon or Nobleman of Crossout to handle problematic monsters.

Late Game (Turns 7+)

  • Primary Goal: Secure the win by protecting Destiny Board and managing the opponent’s resources.

  1. Focus on Protection:

    • Once Destiny Board has 3-4 Spirit Messages on the field, your priority shifts to maintaining the board state. Ensure that your opponent can’t remove Destiny Board or any of the Spirit Messages.
    • Use Dark Bribe, Solemn Judgment, or Starlight Road to counter any backrow destruction attempts (e.g., Mystical Space Typhoon or Heavy Storm).
    • Keep Battle Fader, Threatening Roar, and Waboku handy to prevent direct attacks from breaking through your defenses.

  2. Counter Aggression:

    • If your opponent tries to push aggressively, use cards like Mirror Force, Torrential Tribute, and Book of Moon to disrupt their offense.
    • Stardust Dragon from Starlight Road can act as a big body to block attacks and negate mass destruction effects.

  3. Finish the Game:

    • Once you have all 5 Spirit Messages spelled out, you automatically win the game. Ensure that Destiny Board and your defensive cards are well-protected until this happens.

Matchup-Specific Strategies

Against Aggro Decks (e.g., Blackwings, Gladiator Beasts)

  • Side in: Lightning Vortex and Torrential Tribute to clear the board of swarming monsters.
  • Use Waboku and Threatening Roar early to prevent attacks.
  • Gravekeeper’s Spy and Guard will wall off most of their attackers, while Messenger of Peace stops larger monsters.

Against Graveyard Decks (e.g., Lightsworn, Zombies)

  • Side in: Light-Imprisoning Mirror and D.D. Crow to shut down graveyard reliance.
  • Necrovalley and Kycoo the Ghost Destroyer will stop cards like Judgment Dragon or Mezuki from being used effectively.

Against Control Decks (e.g., Frog Monarchs, Gadgets)

  • Side in: Royal Decree to shut down heavy backrow.
  • Use Dark Bribe and Solemn Judgment to negate cards like Caius the Shadow Monarch or Raiza the Storm Monarch.
  • Keep Battle Fader ready to stop attacks from big tribute monsters.

Key Tech Plays

  • Starlight Road: Timing this card correctly to block mass removal like Heavy Storm not only saves your backrow but also provides you with Stardust Dragon.
  • Gold Sarcophagus: Use it to search Destiny Board or any critical card that you need to solidify your setup.
  • Gravekeeper’s Spy: Use its effect to bring out more Gravekeeper's cards, building up a defensive wall.

General Tips

  • Patience is key: You are playing a slow-paced, stall-based deck, so don’t rush into activating Destiny Board until you have enough protection in place.
  • Anticipate removal: Opponents will often hold their removal cards (Mystical Space Typhoon, Heavy Storm) for Destiny Board, so bait them out by setting other cards and forcing early use of those spells.
  • Graveyard Control: In Edison format, many decks rely heavily on their graveyard. Keep Kycoo or Necrovalley on the field to hinder graveyard manipulation.

By following this strategy, you can consistently protect your Destiny Board win condition while adapting to different matchups. Good resource management and knowing when to activate key cards are crucial to securing victory!

DINOS BEST DECK

The side deck is very experimental, there's a lot of other options, so feel free to switch that up.

With that in note, good luck!

deck_excerpt: Dice Jar OTK ft. Junk Speeder
deck_description:
Hey there! Another old deck, revised for new strategy.

 

 

Gameplan

1) After drawing everything, if you have played "Into the Void" beforehand, set all Traps and end your turn. This results into MJ #2 + Dice Jar being sent to your GY.

2) When it's your opponent's Draw Phase, activate these Traps in explained order below:

  1. Pikeru
  2. Reverse Reuse >>> MJ #2 and Dice as face-down
  3. All-Out Attacks
  4. That Six

3) What is going to happen is that MJ #2 and Dice opens up to trigger themselves, thanks to All-Out. Dice lets both players roll a die, where higher roller is the winner dealing some damage to the opponent. You can adjust die outcomes with That Six, which you should aim for 6 to deal 6000 damage. However, you won't take any effect damage thanks to Pikeru, don't worry.

4) Until your opponent is dead, what was explained in #3 will be an endless loop thanks to MJ #2.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Reinforcement of the Army" can be found by completing the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" can be found either within "The Infinite Void" or "Life Force Control System" Secret Packs to save 90 SR!

  • 3 x Junk Synchron >>> 90 SR

deck_excerpt: Branded Despia got a small consistency boost since Gold Sarcophagus is at 2!
deck_description:
Gold Sarcophagus is now at 2 thanks to the recent Masterduel banlist, granting you another copy of many cards in your deck, including Branded Fusion!

Nearly two years of Branded has existed in Masterduel, and we still get cool new ways to play the archetype! Yubel remains the best way to play Branded, and its powerups is an indirect buff to Albaz and friends. In addition to the regular playstyle of Branded, Yubel can now be used as a monster negate engine - effectively granting the deck an extra 3 copies of Called by the Grave. The Yubel cards are fairly minimal and it is composed of 5 cards. It is comprised of 3 Nightmare Throne, 1 Spirit of Yubel and 1 OG Yubel. Upon activation, Nightmare Throne destroys in deck Spirit of Yubel, which floats into the OG Yubel from deck. From there, a Phantom of Yubel can be summoned, granting Branded another way to deal with handtraps like Ash Blossom! Phantom of Yubel grants a higher success rate for Branded Fusion to successfully resolve - thus winning you more games! 

Yubel can also break boards and bait handtraps, since most gamestates are monster interaction based nowadays, the opposing player will be forced to prematurely use their interruption in an effort to stop Phantom of Yubel from coming out! After Yubel has sufficiently used up your opponent's interruption, you can go for your regular Branded plays unimpeded, without fear of Ash Blossom or Nibiru! 
 
The Yubel cards also aren't really "bricks" since they can be discarded to the GY as part of your Branded combos. If you happen to have both Yubels in the GY (through Branded Fusion, Grass Grows Greener, etc.) you can also make Phantom of Yubel relatively free! 

While not entirely game changing and it doesn't largely change the strategy, the "Yubel engine" grants another layer of protection of Branded. I highly recommend my fellow Branded bros to try out this next evolution of Albaz and friends!
 
Also, if you want a proper guide and combos how to pilot Branded, check out my earlier guide by clicking here.
 
Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
 
GLHF Duelists!

deck_name: Divinidad que desafía la obscuridad (Deck Tistina)
deck_excerpt: Deck Tistina bastante competente para jugadores nuevos.
deck_description:
Es la primera vez que publico un deck en esta página. Realmente me gusta mucho esta estrategia por la capacidad de alcanzar condiciones de victoria muy rápido. Pienso que el motor duro Tistina es bastante bueno, aunque tal vez no se ha explorado lo suficiente como para llegar a una buena combinación/deck. Siento que en algún futuro podría ser meta... pero solo son divagaciones mías.

Capacidad de llegar a condiciones de victoria: 8/10 (Hace OTK de manera consistente, y lo mejor es que incluso en esas circunstancias puedes jugar sin depender de cosas como el Extra Deck).

Resistencia a handtraps: 6/10 (Le afecta mucho, MUCHO el Droll & Lock Bird).

Resistencia a Stun: 7/10 (El deck tiene doble invocación normal si es un monstruo Tistina, invocación desde la mano y cementerio. Por lo tanto, es fácil invocar por sacrificio al Dios de Cristal Tistina. Además, es sencillo limpiar monstruos, magias y trampas gracias al efecto de destrucción de este ultimo).

 

Resistencia a Floogate: 7/10 (El deck puede jugar sobre There Can Be Only One y Skill drain. Puede jugar con Rivalry of Warlords. pero sufre demasiado con Anti-spell fragance y Gozen Match lo mata. afortunadamente esa ultima no se juega mucho.)

Resistencia a Destierro: 6/10 (El deck depende del cementerio. No lo suficiente como para jugar Razonamiento o Pasto, pero le afecta que le tiren Shifter y cartas similares).

Resistencia a efectos rápidos: 5/10 (Al deck le cuesta superar campos con muchas interacciones. Por eso, siempre intenta reducir o mitigar el campo rival, recordando el requisito de la carta de campo para invocar desde el deck al Dios de Cristal Tistina).

Resistencia al ir primero: 6/10 (La construcción está pensada para hacer OTK violentos y ganar en turno 2, pero también tiene capacidades para ir primero. El Semidiós tiene el efecto del Dios de Cristal como efecto rápido si este último está en el campo. Es una interacción poderosa, pero algo difícil de usar. Bien ejecutado, puede cortar turnos por completo. Además, puedes hacer un combo para dejar a los dos en el campo en el turno 1. La trampa que no llevo en la decklist es como un Change of Heart para cartas boca abajo; podrías considerar incluirla en tu construcción si quieres jugar el deck como turno 1.)

Puntuación final: 7/10. Juéguenlo! Es muy divertido y, a pesar de las apariencias, es bastante amigable y competente para jugadores nuevos. Sería incluso mejor si no fuera tan caro, jaja. Fuera de eso, mi mejor rango jugando este deck fue Diamante 3. Si algún día Tistina se vuelve meta en Master Duel, seré yo... y sabrán que habré ganado la gloria.

Thank you and if you have any ideas for the deck leave a comment below but im trying to keep the deck insect only just remember.

This is what Joey Wheeler would play in this modern yugioh format.

Using some of the Metalmorph cards mixed with the Flame Swordsman cards.
Uses White Forest/Azamina "pure." Dragoon package means it's unserious.

Vampires is a deck that uses it's Main Deck as a toolbox unlike most decks which mainly use the ED as their toolbox.
The reason why it's okay to play so many one ofs is because there are more than enough ways to search the pieces.
Solitaire can special summon Uni-Zombie which can either mill Familiar or Retainer which essentially means that you can very easily search any Vampire Spell/Trap or Monster.

The biggest problem this deck has is that each time you summon one of the smaller vampires from the GY you lose cards so you need a critical amount of Vampire cards in your starting hand. Vampire Ghost as an example is a very strong card however you need more Vampire monsters for it to even work + any disruption will often stop you right in your tracks.

The going 2nd cards E-Con, Mind Control, Snatch Steal and Change of Heart work in a very unique way in Vampires because their rank 6 and rank 8 can just use your opponents monsters as if they were the correct level to summon them and those 2 + your Link monsters are going to be your win condition because they enable OTKs

The Synchros are just another toolbox that can come up from time to time but they obv aren't the main focus of the deck, the focus is stealing your opponents monsters and use it to make XYZ and Links.

deck_description:
Good day to you! In this deck, Crusher will crush your opponent's hopes of victory to piles of junk. Heh, get it?

 

 

Gameplan

2) If you don't have any Spells but "Primal Seed" in your hand and you have no Spells in Banish Zone (BZ), Special Summon Ruddy with Librarian + Coral/Cardian and activate Ruddy to fill your BZ with everything, including Spells...

  • In reality, it's impossible to dump all Spells from hand to GY. Thus, this step was optional and you can save 30 UR to not craft Ruddy but try to have a fair share of Spells in your hand.

3) Fetch Spells from BZ to your hand with "Primal Seed" loop. Then, use Crusher to send them from hand to BZ to deal 500 damage for each.

4) Repeat what was explained in #3 until your opponent is dead.

deck_excerpt: A new Level 9 FIRE Dinosaur enters
deck_description:
So, the TCG has gotten a better Level 9 FIRE Dinosaur monster than Jurrac Titano in ROTA. QQ Enneagon is a Level 9 FIRE Dinosaur monster who can reveal a Level 9 monster other than itself in your hand while it is in your hand or GY to Special Summon both it and the revealed monster, locking you into Rank 9 or higher Xyz Monsters for the rest of the turn and a Rank 9 or higher Xyz Monster with it as material gains 900 ATK/DEF. Safe to say, this card is just alright. I’m playing Prediction Princess here, not Generaider. The Xyz lock will prevent you from Linking off your Mereologic Aggregator with a Herald of the Arc Light attached which is an issue. So, the best we can do with it is make a revised version of Evol Prediction Princess or even Dinosaur Prediction Princess and substitute Jurrac Titano in those lists with QQ. Now, I did say before that I really liked Evol Prediction Princess and that it is one of the better versions of Prediction Princess, but looking back on that list, it was just asking for a bit too much. That Deck’s main selling point to me was the power of Evo-Singularity giving you access to a 2 negate Evolzar Lars which protected your board from certain cards like Evenly Matched as well as being interruption itself. That Deck was playing Snake-Eye Ash and Snake-Eyes Poplar, and with both of them limited, that killed that list. I much preferred that to a traditional Diabellstar and Sinful Spoils package because Ash into Poplar into Original Sinful Spoils was literally the entire combo by itself.  But, Diabellstar searching for Original Sinful Spoils just used a bit too many cards for me to consider it the better option. But, with the new Azamina cards, we can have much more consistent access to Evoltile Megachirella who then gives us access to Evolsaur Lios. But we still run into the same issue we previously had which is we need to draw a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell or a way to access Prediction Princess Bibliomuse or else we cannot do full Prediction Princess combo. We are not playing World Legacy Monstrosity in this Deck because of how consistent the Azamina cards are at getting you to both Lios and another monster on field which then translates to a Rank 9. But we are still lacking sufficient access to Bibliomuse and whatnot, so I am opting to play 44 cards in the Main Deck to play more ways to get to a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell while also ensuring that certain bricks don’t show up in our opener like QQ Enneagon. We are playing a lot of non-engine, but even if we cut the non-engine, we would still see the same issue and not open a Prediction Princess card. And we can play a large amount of non-engine because we just need to see Diabellstar or a Sinful Spoils card for our whole Azamina into Evol line. This Deck is absolutely fine. Comparing this to my previous Evol Prediction Princess list, this is so much better and so much more consistent. THIS is the Evol Prediction Princess list that sits next to the great Prediction Princess Decks. And because you really just play around with the Azamina cards and Sinful Spoils cards to get to where you need to go, it feels good to play rather than what I had in mind for the previous iteration of the Deck. 

Let’s say for our sample combo, we have a Deception of the Sinful Spoils and a Prediction Princess Tarotrei and 1 other card to just discard. Activate Deception and use its effect to Tribute Tarotrei from hand to search for Sacred Azamina from Deck. Activate Sacred Azamina revealing Azamina Mu Rcielago in Extra Deck and sending Deception from field to GY. Sacred Azamina then Special Summons Mu Rcielago from Extra Deck who then searches for WANTED: Seeker of Sinful Spoils from Deck on Summon. WANTED grabs Diabellstar the Black Witch from Deck. Banish WANTED from GY and shuffle back Deception from GY into Deck and draw 1 card. Diabellstar sends the card you drew to GY to Summon itself who then searches for Original Sinful Spoils - Snake Eye from Deck on Summon. Activate Original Sinful Spoils sending Mu Rcielago to GY to Special Summon Evoltile Megachirella from Deck. Megachirella Tributes itself and discards a card to Special Summon Evolsaur Lios from Deck. On Summon, Lios sets Evo-Singularity from Deck. Then, use its other effect to send QQ Enneagon from your Deck to the GY to make itself and Diabellstar Level 9’s. Overlay them for Mereologic Aggregator in the EMZ, sending Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck to GY. Herald activates to search for Underworld Ritual of Prediction. Aggregator targets Herald in GY, detaching 1 material to attach Herald from GY to itself. Link Aggregator into Gravity Controller and Herald triggers again to search for Prediction Princess Tarotreith. Activate Underworld Ritual to Ritual Summon Tarotrei from GY by Tributing Tarotreith from hand. End Phase Tarotrei Special Summons Tarotreith from GY face-down. During your opponent’s Standby Phase, you can banish Underworld Ritual from GY to get Prediction Princess Bibliomuse from Deck face-down and Tarotrei flips up Tarotreith who then gets either Pot of the Forbidden or Deus-X Krawler from Deck face-down. And you also have Evo-Singularity for Evolzar Dolka for 2 monster negates, Evolzar Laggia for a Normal/Special Summon or Spell/Trap Card negate, or Evolzar Lars for 2 targeted negates for face-up cards when your opponent activates a card or effect. 

For the Main Deck Monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 2 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's effect in the End Phase. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-downn and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back face-down after being Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s card effects. 1 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute. 1 Pot of the Forbidden which has a Flip Effect that lets you choose between Drawing 2 cards, returning all Spell/Traps on the field to the hand, destroying all monsters your opponent controls, or looking at your opponent's hand and shuffling a card from it back into the Deck. 2 QQ Enneagon. You do not want to draw this card. If you do draw it, it is pretty much over for your entire Azamina into Evol line which is why I want to play 2 copies of it. It doesn’t feel good to play 2, but because we have such consistent access to our Azamina Evol line, drawing this just kills the purpose of the combo because Lios can only send it from Deck. 3 Diabellstar the Black Witch. You can Special Summon her from your hand by sending a card from your hand or field to the GY and on Normal or Special Summon, she can set a Sinful Spoils Spell/Trap from Deck. During your opponent’s turn, if she is sent from her owner’s hand or field to the GY, you can send a card from your hand or field to the GY to Special Summon her. 1 Evolsaur Lios and 1 Evoltile Megachirella. Lios sets either an Evolutionary Bridge or an Evo-Singularity from Deck and during your Main Phase in which it was Normal Summoned or Special Summoned by the effect of a FIRE monster, you can send a FIRE Reptile or Dinosaur monster from your Deck to the GY and then you can make 2 monsters on the field become the same Type and Attribute as that monster. Megachirella can Tribute a Reptile and discard a card to Special Summon a Level 6 or lower FIRE Dinosaur from your Deck. And you can banish it from GY and target a Dragon Xyz Monster you control with no material and attach up to 2 Reptile and/or Dinosaur monsters with different names from your hand and/or GY to that monster as material. But it is one effect per turn and only once that turn. We are only playing 1 of each because drawing them literally does not matter. You are not Normal Summoning for your Azamina Sinful Spoils combo. If you do draw either Lios or Megachirella, you can just use the Azamina line to get to a monster on board for Lios to modulate its Level and that monster’s Level to 9 and you can also put up an omni-negate in the form of Azamina Illia Silvia if you want to (more for interruption or protection on your opponent’s turn than protection for your combo - but it still could). Other than that, Lios sets Evo-Singularity which is just a crazy card that puts more interruptions onto your field. And Megachirella’s GY effect is also crazy. If you have a spent Evolzar on turn 3, you can banish it from GY to attach Lios and a QQ Enneagon from your GY to that Evolzar to refresh all of its negates. Lastly, for handtraps, we have 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring, and 3 Effect Veiler. I am opting to Main Deck the Veilers and siding Impermanence because I just want up my monster count for Deception.

Spell/Traps: For the Sinful Spoils, we have 3 WANTED: Seeker of Sinful Spoils, 1 Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye, and 3 Deception of the Sinful Spoils. WANTED adds a Diabellstar monster from your Deck or GY to your hand and you can banish it from your GY and target a Sinful Spoils Spell/Trap that is banished or in your GY other than WANTED and place it on the bottom of the Deck to draw a card. The draw is very good because it gets you a card to send to Summon Diabellstar. Original Sinful Spoils sends 1 other face-up card you control to the GY to Special Summon a Level 1 FIRE monster from your hand or Deck and you can banish it from Gy to target a Snake-Eye or Diabellstar monster in your GY and add a Level 1 FIRE monster from your Deck to your hand and place the targeted monster on the bottom of your Deck. You will sometimes use the GY effect of Original Sinful Spoils over the activated effect if you draw Diabellstar as your starter because in that case, she will be in GY whereas she usually wouldn’t be if you started with like Deception. Deception Tributes a monster from hand or field to add an Azamina card from Deck to hand. Rest of the card does not matter, especially not its GY effect because we are usually placing it from GY to the bottom of our Deck to draw with WANTED. 1 Sacred Azamina which reveals an Azamina Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck and send a Sinful Spoils card from your hand and/or field to the GY for every 4 Levels that monster has to Special Summon that monster which is treated as a Fusion Summon. And if it is in your GY, you can target an Azamina monster you control or in your GY and shuffle it into the Deck to add this card to your hand. 1 Foolish Burial. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which can Ritual Summon a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. 2 Prediction Ritual which can only Ritual Summon Prediction Princess Tarotrei, and you can banish it from GY except the turn it was sent there to search for a Prediction Princess monster. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites which searches a Ritual Spell from Deck and a Ritual Monster from Deck or GY whose name is mentioned on that card. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 1 Evo-Singularity which targets an Evoltile and Evolsaur in your GY, Special Summoning an Evolzar Xyz Monster from your Extra Deck and attaching the targeted monsters to it as Xyz Material. 

Extra Deck: 1 Azamina Mu Rcielago which decreases the ATK/DEF of all monsters your opponent controls by 500 for each Azamina Monster you control and if it is Fusion Summoned, you can search for an Azamina or a Sinful Spoils card from your Deck, and if it is destroyed by battle or card effect, you can add a Sinful Spoils Spell from your Deck to your hand. 1 Azamina Illia Silvia which doubles the battle damage inflicted to your opponent by your other Azamina monsters. When your opponent activates a card or effect, you can Quick Effect Tribute it to negate the effect, and if it is destroyed by battle or card effect, you can add a Sinful Spoils Trap from your Deck to your hand. I did really consider playing Azamina Sol Erysichthon over Silvia because usually, you wouldn’t have Silvia sticking around as an interruption for your opponent’s turn, and you certainly aren’t Summoning it early enough to really protect your plays. Erysichthon targets and sends a card on the field to the GY on Fusion Summon which gives it a little more usage than Silvia in situations where you can’t keep the second Azamina Fusion Monster you Summon on field, but there are cases where you can keep Silvia around as interruption which made me choose to play it over Erysichthon. 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Evolzar Lars which your opponent cannot target with monster effects while it has material. When your opponent activates a card or effect, you can Quick Effect detach 2 materials or 1 if it only has Reptile or Dino monsters as material to target a face-up card your opponent controls and negate its effects until the end of the turn. 1 Evolzar Laggia which can detach 2 Xyz Materials to negate the Normal or Special Summon of a monster(s) or the activation of a Spell/Trap Card and destroy it. 1 Evolzar Dolkka which can detach a material to negate an activated monster effect and destroy that monster. 1 S:P Little Knight and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Droll & Lock Bird, 2 Crossout Designator, 1 Called by the Grave, 3 Triple Tactics Talent, 3 Infinite Impermanence, and 3 Evenly Matched.
